result.execSummary:
The defendant Charles E. Wacholtz was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case. One or more other charges in this case were dismissed. The dismissed charges were not proven and have no legal effect. Charles E. Wacholtz is presumed innocent of the dismissed charges.

  • Charles E. Wacholtz was found guilty of Ignition Interlock Device Tampering/Failure to Install, an unclassified misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 347.413(1).
  • Charles E. Wacholtz was found guilty of Fail/Report to Jail (Misdemeanor), a class A misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 946.425(1r)(a).
